This paper is likely to belong to the Performance category (cs.PF) as it focuses on improving the performance of deployed systems through automatic configuration tuning. It could also belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing category (cs.DC) as it mentions improving the throughput of distributed systems like Cassandra and Spark. The paper also discusses the recursive bound-and-search algorithm, which is commonly used in software engineering (cs.SE) and the tuning of system configurations, which is relevant to the Database category (cs.DB). Finally, the paper's focus on improving the performance of deployed systems suggests that it could also belong to the Systems and Control category (cs.SY).
